{"type":"message","id":"5f28c36c","parentId":"0b45a264","timestamp":"2026-02-25T00:00:25.037Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The gh command failed with a GraphQL deprecation warning. Let me try a simpler approach to get the PR status.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_fbe5ba84bdab4e4399b69cb1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /home/ubuntu/.openclaw && gh pr view 24218 --repo openclaw/openclaw --json number,title,state,updatedAt,body"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"bailian","model":"qwen3.5-plus","usage":{"input":27594,"output":109,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":27703,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771977613347}}
{"type":"message","id":"5e89398f","parentId":"5f28c36c","timestamp":"2026-02-25T00:00:25.293Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_fbe5ba84bdab4e4399b69cb1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\"body\":\"## Summary\\n\\nFixes sub-agents spawned via `sessions_spawn` ignoring workspace configurations defined in `agents.list[].workspace`.\\n\\n**Problem:** When an agent had a custom workspace path configured (e.g., `~/openclaw-workspace-rs`), spawned sub-agent sessions would default to the parent's workspace instead, causing files to be written to the wrong location and `memory_search` to index incorrect directories.\\n\\n**Solution:** Passes the `workspace` field through the full session lifecycle — both **write path** (spawn → session patch) and **read path** (session entry → reply workspace resolution):\\n\\n### Write path (storing workspace on the session)\\n- `spawnSubagentDirect` now passes `targetAgentConfig?.workspace` to the `sessions.patch` call\\n- `SessionsPatchParamsSchema` accepts an optional `workspace` field\\n- `applySessionsPatchToStore` validates and persists workspace (immutable once set)\\n- `SessionEntry` type extended with optional `workspace` field\\n\\n### Read path (using workspace at execution time)\\n- `getReplyFromConfig` checks `sessionEntry.workspace` after session init\\n- When present, re-resolves `workspaceDir` via `ensureAgentWorkspace` so the sub-agent operates in the configured directory instead of the parent's default\\n\\n### Test coverage\\n- `sessions-patch.test.ts`: 6 new test cases covering set, trim, reject-empty, reject-clear, reject-change, and allow-resetting-same-value\\n\\nCloses #17698\",\"number\":24218,\"state\":\"OPEN\",\"title\":\"fix(agents): respect workspace config for sub-agent sessions\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-02-23T15:34:44Z\"}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":241,"aggregated":"{\"body\":\"## Summary\\n\\nFixes sub-agents spawned via `sessions_spawn` ignoring workspace configurations defined in `agents.list[].workspace`.\\n\\n**Problem:** When an agent had a custom workspace path configured (e.g., `~/openclaw-workspace-rs`), spawned sub-agent sessions would default to the parent's workspace instead, causing files to be written to the wrong location and `memory_search` to index incorrect directories.\\n\\n**Solution:** Passes the `workspace` field through the full session lifecycle — both **write path** (spawn → session patch) and **read path** (session entry → reply workspace resolution):\\n\\n### Write path (storing workspace on the session)\\n- `spawnSubagentDirect` now passes `targetAgentConfig?.workspace` to the `sessions.patch` call\\n- `SessionsPatchParamsSchema` accepts an optional `workspace` field\\n- `applySessionsPatchToStore` validates and persists workspace (immutable once set)\\n- `SessionEntry` type extended with optional `workspace` field\\n\\n### Read path (using workspace at execution time)\\n- `getReplyFromConfig` checks `sessionEntry.workspace` after session init\\n- When present, re-resolves `workspaceDir` via `ensureAgentWorkspace` so the sub-agent operates in the configured directory instead of the parent's default\\n\\n### Test coverage\\n- `sessions-patch.test.ts`: 6 new test cases covering set, trim, reject-empty, reject-clear, reject-change, and allow-resetting-same-value\\n\\nCloses #17698\",\"number\":24218,\"state\":\"OPEN\",\"title\":\"fix(agents): respect workspace config for sub-agent sessions\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-02-23T15:34:44Z\"}","cwd":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1771977625290}}
